cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with identifying human actions visible in online videos, which involves both computer vision (to analyze the visual clues) and natural language processing (to analyze the speech description). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also introduces a multimodal algorithm that leverages information from both visual and linguistic clues, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
